Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on perception and manipulation tasks for robots, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a probabilistic approach for scene estimation, which involves object detection and recognition, a common task in computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper utilizes probabilistic reasoning and maintains beliefs over time, which are common techniques in AI. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses discriminative object detection and recognition, which are machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control of robot physical actions based on scene estimation, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
